summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed to the City of Seattle, executed on December 19, 1910, by Fannie Chandler and C. W. Chandler, her husband, Frank W. Goodhue and Nettie Goodhue, his wife, Wm. L. Gritman and Lena C. Gritman, his wife, George C. Dietrich and Emma M. Dietrich, his wife, and F. S. Hinshilwood and Clara S. Hinshilwood, his wife, for a part of Lots 13, 20 and 21, Plat of B. W. Johns and C. H. Hanford's Five Acre Lots.
